WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.984 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.984 --> 00:00:05.976 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.976 --> 00:00:09.462 align:middle line:10%
[AUDIO LOGO]

00:00:09.462 --> 00:00:11.960 align:middle line:90%


00:00:11.960 --> 00:00:13.450 align:middle line:90%
>> All right.

00:00:13.450 --> 00:00:18.040 align:middle line:10%
So this is from a very
interesting piece that was

00:00:18.040 --> 00:00:22.280 align:middle line:10%
written way back in 1963, "The
World-Year of the Persians."

00:00:22.280 --> 00:00:25.460 align:middle line:84%
It's published in the Journal of
the American Oriental Society.

00:00:25.460 --> 00:00:28.300 align:middle line:84%
"The notion of cyclically
recurrent cosmic disasters,

00:00:28.300 --> 00:00:32.080 align:middle line:84%
a catastrophe by flood
alternating with one by fire--

00:00:32.080 --> 00:00:35.500 align:middle line:84%
has been traced from
ancient Babylonia and Iran

00:00:35.500 --> 00:00:38.020 align:middle line:84%
through Pythagorean
and Stoic philosophy,

00:00:38.020 --> 00:00:43.170 align:middle line:84%
and thence into
the medieval world.

00:00:43.170 --> 00:00:45.700 align:middle line:84%
In classical Greek and
Hellenistic literature,

00:00:45.700 --> 00:00:49.020 align:middle line:84%
the doctrine of the 'Great
Year' was already connected with

00:00:49.020 --> 00:00:51.980 align:middle line:84%
the myths of the
Deluge and Ekpyrosis."

00:00:51.980 --> 00:00:55.880 align:middle line:84%
Now, Deluge is the destruction
of the world by water.

00:00:55.880 --> 00:00:58.600 align:middle line:10%
Ekpyrosis is the destruction
of the world by fire.

00:00:58.600 --> 00:01:01.200 align:middle line:10%
And you know if
you read the Bible,

00:01:01.200 --> 00:01:02.590 align:middle line:10%
it's almost like bookends.

00:01:02.590 --> 00:01:06.870 align:middle line:10%
You've got the Deluge of Noah
in the recounted beginning.

00:01:06.870 --> 00:01:10.890 align:middle line:10%
It's third through seventh
chapters of Genesis.

00:01:10.890 --> 00:01:13.590 align:middle line:10%
And then you've got
the apocalyptic visions

00:01:13.590 --> 00:01:16.050 align:middle line:10%
in the book of Revelations,
which is primarily

00:01:16.050 --> 00:01:18.190 align:middle line:10%
describing destruction by fire.

00:01:18.190 --> 00:01:22.920 align:middle line:84%
And those are the two
bookends of the sacred Judeo--

00:01:22.920 --> 00:01:24.990 align:middle line:90%
the Christian scriptures.

00:01:24.990 --> 00:01:29.460 align:middle line:10%
But those same ideas we find
all over the ancient world.

00:01:29.460 --> 00:01:32.820 align:middle line:10%
This was not something
that was limited to one

00:01:32.820 --> 00:01:34.630 align:middle line:10%
particular cultural group.

00:01:34.630 --> 00:01:37.500 align:middle line:10%
I think the reason for that
is in a very strong case can

00:01:37.500 --> 00:01:40.080 align:middle line:10%
be made is that
yes, there really

00:01:40.080 --> 00:01:43.720 align:middle line:10%
have been tremendous
catastrophes that afflict

00:01:43.720 --> 00:01:45.690 align:middle line:10%
this planet from time to time.

00:01:45.690 --> 00:01:48.490 align:middle line:10%
Our ancestors survived
some of these catastrophes.

00:01:48.490 --> 00:01:53.140 align:middle line:10%
And the catastrophes did
involve gigantic fires

00:01:53.140 --> 00:01:55.020 align:middle line:10%
and gigantic floods.

00:01:55.020 --> 00:01:58.240 align:middle line:10%
So we're going to look a little
bit at the floods, first of all,

00:01:58.240 --> 00:02:02.090 align:middle line:10%
but we're going to see this
what I call the wheel of time.

00:02:02.090 --> 00:02:05.320 align:middle line:10%
And what I've done
is here is I've

00:02:05.320 --> 00:02:08.780 align:middle line:10%
broken up the wheel into 12.

00:02:08.780 --> 00:02:11.590 align:middle line:84%
And you can see
down here is Leo,

00:02:11.590 --> 00:02:16.520 align:middle line:84%
and right up here would be
the cusp of Pisces, Aquarius.

00:02:16.520 --> 00:02:18.620 align:middle line:90%
So this would be 0 years--

00:02:18.620 --> 00:02:20.960 align:middle line:90%
BP stands for Before Present.

00:02:20.960 --> 00:02:26.120 align:middle line:84%
And 25,920 years BP that
would have been one cycle ago.

00:02:26.120 --> 00:02:29.050 align:middle line:84%
The vernal equinox would have
been stationed right in here.

00:02:29.050 --> 00:02:32.290 align:middle line:84%
If we go across this
half of a cycle ago,

00:02:32.290 --> 00:02:38.920 align:middle line:84%
12,960 years before present,
we're within a few decades

00:02:38.920 --> 00:02:42.140 align:middle line:84%
of an event that is known
as the Younger Dryas.

00:02:42.140 --> 00:02:44.030 align:middle line:84%
How many have you
ever heard that term?

00:02:44.030 --> 00:02:46.990 align:middle line:90%
All of you I hope by now.

00:02:46.990 --> 00:02:49.450 align:middle line:10%
There was a time not too
long ago when I said,

00:02:49.450 --> 00:02:51.620 align:middle line:10%
how many have heard
of the Younger Dryas?

00:02:51.620 --> 00:02:52.820 align:middle line:10%
No hands would have gone up.

00:02:52.820 --> 00:02:55.262 align:middle line:10%
So we're making progress here.

00:02:55.262 --> 00:02:58.186 align:middle line:90%
